docs.abstract: Two books explain the contributing factors, while a young adult novel shows the toll it takes on a teenager.
docs.snippet: Two books explain the contributing factors, while a young adult novel shows the toll it takes on a teenager.
docs.lead_paragraph: The devastating gun violence in Chicago once again garnered national attention after 66 were shot, 12 fatally, during a particularly violent weekend earlier this month. Two of these books explain some of the factors that have bred this violence, while a young adult novel gets inside the mind of a teenager caught in its cross hairs.

headline.main: Read These 3 Books About Gun Violence in Chicago

docs.abstract: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.snippet: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After weeks of hype, white supremacists managed to muster just a couple of dozen supporters on Sunday in the nation’s capital for the first anniversary of their deadly rally in Charlottesville, Va., finding themselves greatly outnumbered by counterprotesters, police officers and representatives of the news media.

headline.main: Rally by White Nationalists Was Over Almost Before It Began
headline.print_headline: White Nationalist Rally Drowned Out by Crowd Of Anti-Hate Protesters

docs.abstract: There are consequences to mischaracterizing the reason players aren’t standing.
docs.snippet: There are consequences to mischaracterizing the reason players aren’t standing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Now that the N.F.L. preseason has begun, some of the league’s players are again refusing to stand during the national anthem in protest of police brutality. A number of news organizations have mischaracterized the protests as “anthem protests,” and President Trump has gone further, saying they just “wanted to show their ‘outrage’ at something that most of them are unable to define.” He keeps coming back to this issue over and over.

headline.main: Football Players Are Protesting Police Violence, Not the Anthem

docs.abstract: My father spied on activists for the Memphis Police Department in the 1960s. A new lawsuit suggests not much has changed.
docs.snippet: My father spied on activists for the Memphis Police Department in the 1960s. A new lawsuit suggests not much has changed.
docs.lead_paragraph: I’ve often wondered about the 10 file cabinets of domestic surveillance records that officials in the Memphis Police Department doused with fuel and burned in 1976, the year I was born. What portion was related to my father, Marrell McCollough?

headline.main: The Memphis Police Spied on Activists

docs.abstract: The polymath musician is a whole new model of artist, daubing his signature sensibility over music, film, dance and everything else he touches.
docs.snippet: The polymath musician is a whole new model of artist, daubing his signature sensibility over music, film, dance and everything else he touches.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a sticky late-spring Saturday in New York, Devonté Hynes was on the set of the video for the song “Jewelry,” one of his newest solo recordings under the name Blood Orange — a typically restless, jazzy slow jam that starts as a spoken-word poem and ends as a kind of languid rap. The “set,” in this case, meant the sidewalk on a slip of street running west to east between Sixth Avenue and Washington Square Park. As with most of the videos the 32-year-old Hynes has created since he began making music professionally, back in his late teens, he was directing this one himself.

headline.main: How Dev Hynes, English Misfit, Became Blood Orange, R.&B. Miracle Worker

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In 2016, American intelligence agencies delivered urgent and explicit warnings about Russia’s intentions to try to tip the American presidential election — and a detailed assessment of the operation afterward — thanks in large part to informants close to President Vladimir V. Putin and in the Kremlin who provided crucial details.

docs.abstract: It’s time to update our stereotypes.
docs.snippet: It’s time to update our stereotypes.
docs.lead_paragraph: I used to love nerds. Or at least, I loved the idea of nerds. In the ’80s, ’90s and 2000s, there was an endless stream of movies and media, from “Revenge of the Nerds” to “Spider-Man” to “Beauty and the Geek,” dedicated to telling women that they’d be better off with nerds than with the arrogant jocks who would grunt cavemanlike in response to anything women said, before kicking sand in a nerd’s face.

docs.abstract: Mr. Bell defeated Robert P. McCulloch, the county official who oversaw the investigation into the police shooting of Michael Brown in 2014.
docs.snippet: Mr. Bell defeated Robert P. McCulloch, the county official who oversaw the investigation into the police shooting of Michael Brown in 2014.
docs.lead_paragraph: Wesley Bell, a reform-minded City Council member from Ferguson, Mo., declared victory in the Democratic primary for St. Louis County prosecutor Tuesday evening, saying he had ousted the longtime incumbent Robert P. McCulloch, who came under national scrutiny for his handling of the investigation into the 2014 shooting of a black teenager by a white police officer.

headline.main: Wesley Bell, Ferguson Councilman, Unseats St. Louis County Prosecutor
